hopobject.body: Not available at the moment oral solu medrol for ms But Holly’s condition only worsened. Over the next few days her fever climbed, and she started to vomit and have diarrhea. Jess carried Holly to the clinic two more times. On the third visit, Holly was so ill that she was transported to the hospital by ambulance — a relative luxury in a country where the health system is woefully under-resourced. None of Jess’s other three children had ever been so sick, and Jess feared for Holly’s life.Â
